{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Y37BaFFvMhTYkKL55NmwfU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01PoRdXQrHUDw4iuDC7ETxGL","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"theorem_title":"Two-point logarithmic Sobolev inequality","theorem_statement":"Let \(\mu\) be the uniform probability measure on \(\{-1,1\}\). For \(f:\{-1,1\}\to\mathbb{R}\), define \(\operatorname{Ent}_{\mu}(f^2):=\mathbb{E}_{\mu}[f^2\log f^2]-\mathbb{E}_{\mu}[f^2]\log(\mathbb{E}_{\mu}[f^2])\) (with \(0\log 0:=0\)). Then \[\operatorname{Ent}_{\mu}(f^2)\le\tfrac{1}{2}(f(1)-f(-1))^2.\]","root_node_id":"root","nodes":"[
  {
    "id": "root",
    "title": "Two-point logarithmic Sobolev inequality",
    "informal_statement": "Let \(a=f(1)\), \(b=f(-1)\). Then \[\operatorname{Ent}_{\mu}(f^2)=\frac{1}{2}\Bigl(a^2\log(a^2)+b^2\log(b^2)-(a^2+b^2)\log\!\tfrac{a^2+b^2}{2}\Bigr)\le\frac{(a-b)^2}{2}.\]",
    "informal_proof_text": "Since \(\mu\) is uniform, \(\mathbb{E}_\mu[f^2]=(a^2+b^2)/2\) and \(\mathbb{E}_\mu[f^2\log f^2]=(a^2\log(a^2)+b^2\log(b^2))/2\). Multiplying through by \(2\), the entropy inequality is exactly the scalar two-variable inequality\[a^2\log(a^2)+b^2\log(b^2)-(a^2+b^2)\log\!\tfrac{a^2+b^2}{2}\le(a-b)^2.\]This follows from the normalized one-variable inequality (node `scalar_ineq`) by: (i) sign reduction — the left side depends only on \(a^2,b^2\), so replacing \((a,b)\) by \((|a|,|b|\)) leaves it unchanged while \((|a|-|b|)^2\le(a-b)^2\); (ii) homogeneity — both sides scale as \(c^2\) under \((a,b)\mapsto(ca,cb)\), so we may normalize \(a^2+b^2=2\); (iii) substituting \(u=a^2\in[0,2]\) and applying the normalized inequality.",
    "display_label": "Main theorem"
  },
  {
    "id": "scalar_ineq",
    "title": "Normalized one-variable inequality \(G(u)\ge 0\)",
    "informal_statement": "Define, for \(u\in[0,2]\), \[G(u):=\bigl(\sqrt{u}-\sqrt{2-u}\bigr)^2-u\log u-(2-u)\log(2-u)\] (with \(0\log 0:=0\)). Then \(G(u)\ge 0\) for all \(u\in[0,2]\).",
    "informal_proof_text": "Note \(G\) is continuous on \([0,2]\), smooth on \((0,2)\), and symmetric under \(u\mapsto 2-u\). At the center, \(G(1)=(\sqrt{1}-\sqrt{1})^2-0-0=0\). By the convexity lemma (node `G_convex`), \(G''(u)\ge 0\) on \((0,2)\), so \(G\) is convex. One computes \(G'(1)=2(1-1)/\sqrt{1\cdot 1}-\log(1/1)=0\). A convex function whose derivative vanishes at an interior point attains its global minimum there. Hence \(G(u)\ge G(1)=0\) for all \(u\in[0,2]\).",
    "display_label": "\(G(u)\ge 0\) on \([0,2]\)"
  },
  {
    "id": "G_convex",
    "title": "Convexity: \(G''(u)\ge 0\) on \((0,2)\)",
    "informal_statement": "For \(u\in(0,2)\), the second derivative of \(G\) satisfies \[G''(u)=\frac{2\bigl(1-\sqrt{u(2-u)}\bigr)}{\bigl(u(2-u)\bigr)^{3/2}}\ge 0.\]",
    "informal_proof_text": "Using \((\sqrt{u}-\sqrt{2-u})^2=2-2\sqrt{u(2-u)}\), one computes\[\frac{d}{du}\bigl(\sqrt{u}-\sqrt{2-u}\bigr)^2=\frac{2(u-1)}{\sqrt{u(2-u)}},\quad\frac{d}{du}\bigl(u\log u+(2-u)\log(2-u)\bigr)=\log\frac{u}{2-u},\]giving \(G'(u)=\frac{2(u-1)}{\sqrt{u(2-u)}}-\log\frac{u}{2-u}\). Differentiating again:\[\frac{d}{du}\frac{2(u-1)}{\sqrt{u(2-u)}}=\frac{2}{(u(2-u))^{3/2}},\quad\frac{d}{du}\log\frac{u}{2-u}=\frac{1}{u}+\frac{1}{2-u}=\frac{2}{u(2-u)}.\]Hence \(G''(u)=\frac{2}{(u(2-u))^{3/2}}-\frac{2}{u(2-u)}=\frac{2(1-\sqrt{u(2-u)})}{(u(2-u))^{3/2}}\). Since \(u(2-u)=1-(u-1)^2\le 1\) for \(u\in[0,2]\), we have \(\sqrt{u(2-u)}\le 1\), so \(G''(u)\ge 0\).",
    "display_label": "\(G''(u)\ge 0\)"
  }
]","edges":[{"source_id":"G_convex","target_id":"scalar_ineq","label":"convexity of G","explanation":"G'' ≥ 0 implies G is convex, which with G'(1)=0 gives G(1)=0 as global minimum."},{"source_id":"scalar_ineq","target_id":"root","label":"normalized scalar inequality → main entropy bound","explanation":"After sign reduction and homogeneity normalization, the entropy inequality reduces to G(u) ≥ 0."}],"candidates":[{"node_id":"scalar_ineq","priority":1,"rationale":"The core one-variable inequality G(u) ≥ 0 is the central formal island: it encodes the entire scalar reduction and the convexity-plus-minimum argument, and its statement is a clean, self-contained real inequality that would directly discharge the main theorem once formalized."},{"node_id":"G_convex","priority":2,"rationale":"The explicit second derivative computation G''(u) = 2(1−√(u(2−u)))/(u(2−u))^(3/2) ≥ 0 is the technically nontrivial step; it requires careful differentiation and the AM-GM bound u(2−u) ≤ 1, making it a high-value formal verification target."}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":4916,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d59f08f1-0f4a-4bea-8683-b342e4abb969","uuid":"32b15be9-cb03-46c4-bb3b-e8e6eeb8ede3"}

